<TITLE> Court clears way for Hasina to go abroad </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 9 (bdnews24.com) -- A Dhaka judge Monday exempted former prime minister Sheikh Hasina from personal appearance in court in the barge-mounted power plants graft case, clearing the way for her to travel abroad for better medical treatment. Hasina's lawyers also filed an appeal for exemption in the Niko scam case. The lawyers moved to seek similar exemption for her in other cases as well. bd
